.TH BAO 1 "2026-03-31" "bao 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bao \- local-first experiment tracker with a git-like CLI subset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bao
.I command
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBbao\fR is a local-first CLI that tracks experiment runs and evaluations.
It provides a subset of git-like commands for staging files and creating
content-addressed commits under \fI.bao/\fR.
.P
\fBbao\fR is not a full Git implementation. Network operations and history graph
semantics are intentionally limited in this prototype.
.SH REPOSITORY
A Bao repository is a directory containing \fI.bao/\fR.
.TP
\fI.bao/HEAD\fR
Current branch (symbolic ref) or detached commit hash.
.TP
\fI.bao/refs/heads/\fR
Branch references (files containing a commit hash).
.TP
\fI.bao/refs/tags/\fR
Tag references.
.TP
\fI.bao/staged\fR
Staging area (index) storing one relative path per line.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Initialize a repository in \fI.bao/\fR.
.TP
.B add
Stage paths.
Supports \fB-A\fR/\fB--all\fR, \fB-u\fR/\fB--update\fR, \fB-n\fR/\fB--dry-run\fR, \fB-v\fR.
.TP
.B commit
Create a commit from the staging area.
Supports \fB-m\fR, \fB-F\fR/\fB--file\fR, \fB-a\fR/\fB--all\fR, \fB-q\fR, \fB--amend\fR, \fB--edit\fR, \fB--no-edit\fR.
.RS
If \fB-m\fR/\fB-F\fR is omitted, \fBbao\fR generates a default message summarizing staged paths.
If an editor is available (\fB$BAO_EDITOR\fR, \fB$EDITOR\fR, or \fB$VISUAL\fR), you can edit the generated message (use \fB--edit\fR to force).
To disable editor usage (CI), set \fBBAO_NO_EDITOR=1\fR or pass \fB--no-edit\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B log
Show commit history (time-ordered).
Supports \fB-n\fR/\fB--max-count\fR, \fB-1\fR, \fB--oneline\fR.
.TP
.B status
Show branch/HEAD and staged paths.
Supports \fB-s\fR/\fB--short\fR, \fB-b\fR/\fB--branch\fR, \fB--porcelain\fR.
.TP
.B checkout
Switch branches or detach at a commit.
Supports \fB-b\fR, \fB-B\fR, \fB--detach\fR.
.TP
.B switch
\fBgit switch\fR-like interface.
Supports \fB-c\fR, \fB-C\fR, \fB--detach\fR.
.TP
.B branch
List/create/delete/rename branches.
Supports \fB-d\fR/\fB-D\fR, \fB-m\fR/\fB-M\fR, \fB-v\fR, \fB-c\fR.
.TP
.B tag
List/create/delete tags.
Supports \fB-l\fR, \fB-d\fR/\fB--delete\fR.
.TP
.B show
Show a commit object.
Supports \fB--stat\fR, \fB--name-only\fR.
.TP
.B diff
Show differences between commits or between HEAD and index (\fB--cached\fR).
.TP
.B reset
Move HEAD and/or clear the staging area.
Supports \fB--soft\fR, \fB--mixed\fR, \fB--hard\fR.
.TP
.B restore
Restore the staging area.
Supports \fB--staged\fR, \fB--source\fR.
.TP
.B rm
Remove paths from disk and/or staging.
Supports \fB--cached\fR, \fB-r\fR, \fB-f\fR.
.TP
.B stash
Manage a single stash snapshot for the staging area:
\fBlist\fR, \fBpush\fR, \fBpop\fR, \fBapply\fR, \fBdrop\fR, \fBclear\fR.
.TP
.B remote
Manage remotes stored in \fI.bao/remotes\fR:
\fBadd\fR, \fBrm\fR, \fBrename\fR, \fBset-url\fR, \fBget-url\fR, \fBshow\fR.
.TP
.B version
Print version.
.TP
.B help
Show a brief help text.
.SH SECURITY NOTES
\fBbao\fR only accepts repository-relative paths for staging and removal.
Absolute paths, path traversal (\fB..\fR), backslashes, control characters,
and direct operations on \fI.bao/\fR are rejected.
.SH LIMITATIONS
This prototype does not implement a full Git working tree, merge/rebase/cherry-pick,
or network fetch/push/pull.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I bao.yaml
Project configuration (model, prompts, dataset settings).
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgit\fR(1)
